This paper deals with voting systems, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The use of tournament solutions to help voters make decisions involves algorithms and decision-making processes, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study of axiomatic properties and complexity of control and bribery problems falls under the category of theoretical computer science (cs.DS). The use of voting systems to select candidates can also be seen as a machine learning problem (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's focus on voting systems and decision-making processes could also be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
